293: Escherichia coli strain SMG017F3, isolated from rectal swab of a patient with UTI
Identifiers: BioSample: SAMN18221695; Sample name: SMG017F3
Organism: Escherichia coli
Attributes:
    /strain="SMG017F3"
    /host="Homo sapiens"
    /isolation source="rectal swab"
    /collection date="2020"
    /geographic location="Brazil"
    /sample type="single cell"
    /collected by="Universidade Federal de Sao Paulo"
    /genotype="Extraintestinal Pathogenic Escherichia coli"
    /latitude and longitude="22.371944 S 46.941944 W"
    /serotype="O1:K1:H7"
Description:
This strain is part of a comparative study evaluating E. coli clones isolated from the gut of hospitalized patients with strains causing urinary tract infection in one single center. The Escherichia coli strain SMG017F3 was isolated from a rectal swab from an inpatient with a urinary tract infection. This sequence refers to clone F3 from the patient SMG017. The other clones isolated from the rectal swab of the same inpatient are SMG017F1, SMG017F2, and SMG017F8. The strain isolated from the urine is SMG017U.
Accession: SAMN18221695	ID: 18221695
